  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A requirement mandates experimental-validation as the verification method for hemolysis output comparison; however, the supporting validation activity relied on a structured literature review of published hemolysis datasets rather than direct experimental testing. The narrative characterises the two approaches as complementary evidence streams, but the structured activity type does not satisfy the requirement's prescribed method.",
