    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the literature review provided sufficient comparative evidence for hemolysis prediction credibility, noting broad agreement within ±18% across surveyed operating points and the supporting Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification. All credibility factors were reviewed; while achieved levels fall below required levels in multiple areas, the team judged the combined evidence adequate for the intended submission. The structured requirement for experimental-validation was noted but the literature-based comparison was treated as functionally equivalent.",
